COPS have arrested two suspects for illicit drug trafficking between the Eastern Cape and Western Cape on Monday. The Hawks led multidisciplinary operation that included crime intelligence, Eden cluster combating team and the Provincial traffic officials was alerted about a large consignment of dagga that was on transit to George. The two suspects aged between the ages of 35 and 42 were stopped and arrested in Knysna. According to Captain Philani Nkwalase they were found with 18 bags of dagga valued around R965 000. “The suspects’ vehicle as well as all dagga bags we seized for further investigation,” Nkwalase said. The duo is expected to appear at Knysna Magistrates Court on Wednesday on a charge of dealing in dagga.  